other_tests.findings: The hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits. The contour of the liver is smooth. There is no focal liver mass. The main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. There is no ascites. There is no intrahepatic biliary dilation. The CHD measures 5 mm. There is no evidence of stones or gallbladder wall thickening. Positive sonographic ___ sign is elicited. The head and body of the pancreas are within normal limits. The tail of the pancreas is not visualized due to the presence of gas. Normal echogenicity of the spleen, measuring 10.3 cm. Limited views of the bilateral kidneys demonstrate no hydronephrosis.
